trans-unit.source: Restore Azure BizTalk Service from Backup
trans-unit.target: Restore Azure BizTalk Service from Backup

trans-unit.source: This topic provides information on how to restore <token>af_integration</token> from a service backup.
trans-unit.target: This topic provides information on how to restore <token>af_integration</token> from a service backup.

trans-unit.source: You can upgrade the edition as part of the restore.
trans-unit.target: You can upgrade the edition as part of the restore.

trans-unit.source: The following restore upgrades are supported:
trans-unit.target: The following restore upgrades are supported:

trans-unit.source: Basic edition can be restored to Standard edition.
trans-unit.target: Basic edition can be restored to Standard edition.

trans-unit.source: Basic edition can be restored to Premium edition.
trans-unit.target: Basic edition can be restored to Premium edition.

trans-unit.source: Standard edition can be restored to Premium.
trans-unit.target: Standard edition can be restored to Premium.

trans-unit.source: You cannot restore the <embeddedLabel>Developer</embeddedLabel> or <embeddedLabel>Free</embeddedLabel> editions of <token>af_integration</token>.
trans-unit.target: You cannot restore the <embeddedLabel>Developer</embeddedLabel> or <embeddedLabel>Free</embeddedLabel> editions of <token>af_integration</token>.

trans-unit.source: For example, the Premium edition cannot be restored to Standard, Basic, or Developer editions.
trans-unit.target: For example, the Premium edition cannot be restored to Standard, Basic, or Developer editions.

trans-unit.source: The Standard edition cannot be restored to the Basic or Developer editions.
trans-unit.target: The Standard edition cannot be restored to the Basic or Developer editions.

trans-unit.source: The Basic edition cannot be restored to the Developer edition.
trans-unit.target: The Basic edition cannot be restored to the Developer edition.

trans-unit.source: You cannot backup the Developer and Free editions of <token>af_integration</token>.
trans-unit.target: You cannot backup the Developer and Free editions of <token>af_integration</token>.

trans-unit.source: Hence, they cannot be restored as well.
trans-unit.target: Hence, they cannot be restored as well.

trans-unit.source: This section provides information about the request operation to restore <token>af_integration</token>.
trans-unit.target: This section provides information about the request operation to restore <token>af_integration</token>.

trans-unit.source: <legacyItalic>cloud-service-name</legacyItalic> is the unique name for the cloud service that hosts your BizTalk Service.
trans-unit.target: <legacyItalic>cloud-service-name</legacyItalic> is the unique name for the cloud service that hosts your BizTalk Service.

trans-unit.source: The name can be up to 64 characters in length.
trans-unit.target: The name can be up to 64 characters in length.

trans-unit.source: The name must be unique and must range between 6 and 20 characters in length.
trans-unit.target: The name must be unique and must range between 6 and 20 characters in length.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the version of the operation to use for this request.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the version of the operation to use for this request.

trans-unit.target: Specifies an ID to identify the request.

trans-unit.source: You must adhere to the following considerations when providing a backup name:
trans-unit.target: You must adhere to the following considerations when providing a backup name:

trans-unit.source: Backup name must start with a letter or number, and can contain only letters, numbers, and the dash (-) character.
trans-unit.target: Backup name must start with a letter or number, and can contain only letters, numbers, and the dash (-) character.

trans-unit.source: Every dash (-) character must be immediately preceded and followed by a letter or number; consecutive dashes are not permitted in container names.
trans-unit.target: Every dash (-) character must be immediately preceded and followed by a letter or number; consecutive dashes are not permitted in container names.

trans-unit.source: All letters in a container name must be lowercase.
trans-unit.target: All letters in a container name must be lowercase.

trans-unit.source: Length of container names can be between 3 and 63 characters.
trans-unit.target: Length of container names can be between 3 and 63 characters.

trans-unit.source: This represents a custom endpoint for message processing and should not be more than 256 characters in length.
trans-unit.target: This represents a custom endpoint for message processing and should not be more than 256 characters in length.

trans-unit.source: If no value is provided, this is set to <legacyItalic><BizTalkServiceName>.biztalk.windows.net</legacyItalic>.
trans-unit.target: If no value is provided, this is set to <legacyItalic><BizTalkServiceName>.biztalk.windows.net</legacyItalic>.

trans-unit.source: This section lists the error codes that you might encounter while performing backup operations on <token>af_integration</token>.
trans-unit.target: This section lists the error codes that you might encounter while performing backup operations on <token>af_integration</token>.

trans-unit.source: One or more of the service settings specified are not allowed for a restore operation.
trans-unit.target: One or more of the service settings specified are not allowed for a restore operation.

trans-unit.target: Please refer to the product documentation on the allowed values and updatable settings.

trans-unit.target: During a restore, you specify the ACS Namespace and key, SQL database, and storage account.
